snippet.textDisplay: Oh hell no! I’m from the UK and we don’t call it sugared; it’s either sweet or salty. People mostly tend to take their own “share bags” (ours are a lot smaller than the USA sized ones!) of chocolate in eg Nestle Munchies, Galaxy Minstrels, Aero Bubbles, Cadbury’s Wispa Bites/Buttons/Twirl, Terry’s Chocolate Orange Minis, Maltesers, etc or some cheap chewy or hard sweets - all often bought at places like Poundland. Same with drinks...unless it’s a Tango Ice Blast - the blue and green mixed together...THE best!
